claim.claim-text:
15. A method of forming a plastic product, comprising the steps of: 
Extruding a plastic structural body from a manifold of an extrusion-molding unit, with one or more cavities formed inside a sidewall of said structural body; 
Injecting hot air into the cavities of the structural body through an injection pipe connected to the manifold, thus expanding the structural body; 
Cutting both end portions of the structural body after feeding the expanded structural body from the manifold to a mold-forming unit; 
Forming one or more holes on the sidewall of the structural body using one or more perforating and injecting units provided at the mold-forming unit; 
Injecting hot fluid into the cavities of the structural body, thus blowing the structural body; 
Injecting low temperature air into the cavities of the structural body using the perforating and injecting units, and spraying low temperature air to the interior or exterior of the mold-forming unit by an air spraying unit, thus cooling the structural body; and 
Ejecting the structural body from the mold-forming unit, 
Whereby a desired plastic product having one or more sealed cavities inside its completely sealed sidewall is produced.

16. A device for forming a plastic product, comprising: 
An extrusion-molding unit used for extruding a plastic structural body having one or more cavities inside its sidewall; 
An injection pipe connected to an extrusion head of said extrusion molding unit, and used for injecting hot air into the cavities of the structural body to expand the structural body; 
A mold-forming unit installed to seat and mold the structural body fed from said extrusion molding unit; 
A plurality of perforating and injecting units provided at the mold-forming unit for forming a plurality of holes on the sidewall of the structural body, and injecting hot air into the cavities of the structural body to expand the structural body, and injecting a filler into the cavities of the structural body; and 
A feeding unit used for feeding the structural body from the extrusion-molding unit to the mold-forming unit, 
Whereby the device continuously performs one or more processes selected from an extrusion molding process, a blow molding process, a mold-forming process and a filling process, thus producing a desired plastic product having one or more sealed cavities inside its completely sealed and continuous sidewall.

18. The device according to claim 17, wherein said rib thickness adjusting unit comprises: 
The injection pipe bent to have both a rotating support part and a bent part, said rotating support part longitudinally extending through the central axis of each of a plurality of cores, and said bent part extending in a transverse direction of the cores; 
A double gear unit having a first bevel gear and a feed screw, said double gear unit being fitted over the rotating support part of the injection pipe, and rotatably held by middle and rear connectors of each of said cores; 
A second bevel gear mounted on a shaft in each of the cores, and engaging with said first bevel gear; 
A plurality of communication hole forming plates coupled to the middle connector of each of the cores by means of hinge pins such that the communication hole forming plates are openable in opposite directions; 
A feeding nut engaging with said feed screw of the double gear unit; and 
A lever hinged to both the communication hole forming plates and opposite ends of said feed screw at its opposite ends.

19. The device according to claim 17, wherein said rib thickness adjusting unit comprises: 
A couple of drive shafts longitudinally and rotatably connected to the cores of the manifold; 
A guide part provided in a mounting cavity of each of the cores; 
Two sliders fitted over middle part of said drive shafts, and assembled with opposite sides of said guide part such that the sliders are linearly movable in a longitudinal direction; 
A communication hole forming member coupled to a rear portion of each of the cores by a shaft pin, and having a connection arm at one end thereof, with a hemispherical connector provided at the tip of said connection arm and movably coupled to a connection groove of each of the sliders; and 
A drive unit used for rectilinearly moving each of said drive shafts.

21. The device according to claim 16, wherein said feeding unit comprises: 
A plurality of feeding guide rollers+ arranged between the extrusion molding unit and the mold-forming unit, and used for feeding the plastic structural body from the extrusion molding unit to the mold-forming unit; 
A roller supporter used for supporting said feeding guide rollers such that the rollers are movable in a vertical direction in a predetermined stroke; 
A plurality of feeding bars arranged between said guide rollers, and used for feeding the structural body from the extrusion molding unit to the mold-forming unit in cooperation with said guide rollers; and 
A truck unit provided at each side of the roller supporter, and used for supporting the feeding bars such that the feeding bars are movable in longitudinal and transverse directions of a structural body feeding passage.

22. The device according to claim 16, wherein each of said perforating and injecting units comprises: 
An outer pipe mounted to a top mold of the mold-forming unit; 
A middle support pipe fitted in said outer pipe; 
A cutting pipe set in a cylindrical gap between the outer pipe and the middle support pipe such that the cutting pipe is movable in a vertical direction, said cutting pipe having a cutting blade at its lower end; 
A hot air injection pipe fitted in the middle support pipe, and tightened to the middle support pipe at its upper end through a screw-type engagement; 
A filler injection pipe fitted in the hot air injection pipe, and tightened to said hot air injection pipe at its upper end through a screw-type engagement; 
A first lifting unit used for moving the cutting pipe in the vertical direction; 
A rotating unit used for rotating the cutting pipe; 
A second lifting unit used for moving the outer pipe in the vertical direction; and 
A third lifting unit used for moving the middle support pipe in the vertical direction, thus moving both the hot air injection pipe and the filler injection pipe in the same direction.

26. The device according to claim 16, wherein said mold-forming unit comprises: 
At least one cutter provide at each end at both the top and bottom molds; 
Two longitudinal slide blocks provided along opposite sides of each of the top and bottom molds such that the blocks are movable in opposite directions by first actuators; 
A movable core provided at a middle portion of each of the top and bottom molds so as to be movable upward and downward by a second actuator; and 
A clip groove formed at each end of said top and bottom molds at a position outside the cutter, and used for holding both end portions of the plastic structural body while cutting both end portions of the body by the cutter.
